   {:e #blake3 "e499beb4afdb72e85a2637abaa6a0aa568714964053b2e3bdf0b5826bd5c130a" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: DOGFOOD-2 scored 3.48/10 due to concept collapse. Root cause: hardcoded join_threshold=0.20 is a C9 violation — a claim about the embedding space exempt from the system's own verification. ADR-FOUNDATION-031 establishes that parameters are first-class knowledge, subject to the same observe-reconcile-calibrate loop as any other claim.\n\nThis EPIC implements ADR-FOUNDATION-031 for the concept join threshold as the first instance: (1) formalize the ADR as a spec element, (2) replace the hard cutoff with sigmoid soft membership, (3) add Otsu auto-calibration at harvest, (4) revise innate descriptions for better initial centroids, (5) add Narrow collapse diagnostic, (6) test, (7) dogfood retest.\n\nALGEBRAIC STRUCTURE: The threshold is a point in the unit interval [0,1]. The calibration function is a map calibrate: Store -> [0,1] that computes the optimal split from the observed cosine distribution. The sigmoid is a smooth approximation to the Heaviside step function parameterized by (threshold, temperature). Bootstrap defaults are the prior; calibrated values are the posterior.\n\nDELIVERABLES: 1 ADR + 5 implementation tasks + 1 test task + 1 dogfood retest = 8 tasks." :op :assert}
